Writing kinda boils down to following some guidelines anon.
>Think of at least two characters for a story
>Flesh them out regarding personality, quirks, wishes, so on
>Know how they would react to any stimulus and ground them in reality, aka, don't make em good at literally everything and have them with a flaw or two
>Make up a reason or an event to bring the two characters together, assuming you did not have them know each other before
>Sequence the story as points, like A, B, C, D and with you crafting both the scenes at points A B C D AND making the in-between
>'A' could be a meetup at a jog or something, then you'd craft the middle between scene 'B', which could be a coffee shop meeting, planned or unplanned
>Make sure that you stick to one tense, either present or past, either first second or third person.
>Use proper punctuation and a spellchecker. An additional one post Word is advised to check stuff it missed or autocorrected wrong, I use Grammarly
>Write with your own style but don't use that as an excuse to just do purple prose or fill it with nothings like "Basically anon put his benis in her bagina :DD", that's dumb

I ain't the best, having only released two fics but that's what I think I can safely say about writing, even as an amateur.
